This paper proposes a novel way of training a supervised classifier in a distributed setting while preserving user privacy. The paper focuses on machine learning and privacy, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper addresses privacy concerns, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category. The paper also involves communication between clients and a server, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) sub-category. The paper's focus on privacy and communication between clients and a server also suggests that it could belong to the cs.CY (Computers and Society) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves large-scale online evaluation, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category.
